17 Amend the amendment by inserting after section 3 the following:
18 'Sec. 4. Department of Professional and Financial Regulation; rules. The
19 Department of Professional and Financial Regulation shall adopt rules to establish a
20 method for determining the net worth of an entity, together with affiliated and related
21 entities, claiming an exemption from the fees required by the Maine Revised Statutes, Title
22 10, section 9090-A, subsection 1 and 9094-B, subsection 1. The rules must include the
23 evidence and documentation necessary for a purchaser of a manufactured housing
24 community or a mobile home park to provide to the register of deeds when offering a deed
25 for recordation and the record-keeping obligations of the register of deeds. When
26 developing rules, the department shall consider whether information on the incorporation
27 of the entity is useful. Rules adopted pursuant to this section are routine technical rules as
28 defined in Title 5, chapter 375, subchapter 2-A.'
29 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
30 section number to read consecutively.
31 SUMMARY
3322 This amendment amends Committee Amendment "A" and removes the January 1, 2026
3333 start date. It clarifies that an entity claiming an exemption from the fee based on the entity's
3344 net worth includes the net worth of affiliated and related entities. It adds a requirement that
3355 a purchaser claiming an exemption from the fee based on net worth must provide the
3366 register of deeds with an attestation of the entity's net worth at the time the deed for the
3377 manufactured housing community or mobile home park is offered for recordation. It
3388 requires the Department of Professional and Financial Regulation to adopt rules to establish
3399 the method and required evidence and documentation for a purchaser claiming an
4400 exemption to the fee to provide to the register of deeds. It requires the State Controller,
